# Full VAPT Assessment Report

A vulnerability assessment and penetration test was conducted on the DVWA application.

During scanning several vulnerabilities were identified including SQL Injection.

Using sqlmap the SQL injection vulnerability was exploited and database names were extracted successfully.

This demonstrates that user input validation was not implemented properly.

Impact

Attackers could access sensitive database information.

Remediation

Implement prepared statements and input validation.

Regular security testing should be conducted to prevent future attacks.
